<div class="p text-right font-secondary"><a href="table/T7/" class="usa-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open in a new tab</a></div>
<div class="tw-foot p"><div class="fn" id="TFN5"><p id="P110"><strong><em>C</em></strong> = # concepts; <strong><em>V</em></strong> = # overlapping concepts; <strong><em>D</em></strong> = # overlapping roots; <em><strong>V</strong><sub>err</sub></em> = # erroneous overlapping concepts; <strong><em>E</em></strong> = total # errors; <em><strong>D</strong><sub>err</sub></em> = # erroneous overlapping roots; <em><strong>E</strong><sub>root</sub></em> = # errors at the roots;</p></div></div></section><p id="P57">For the entire set of overlapping concepts summarized in the bottom row of <a href="#T7" class="usa-link">Table 7</a>, 127 out of 210 (60%) were found to be erroneous. This result is applicable in assessing Hypothesis 1 (as shown in <a href="#T8" class="usa-link">Table 8</a>).</p>
<section class="tw xbox font-sm" id="T8"><h4 class="obj_head">Table 8.</h4>
<div class="caption p"><p id="P111">Auditing results for overlapping concepts vs. control sample (Phase 2)</p></div>
